media.altText:
I suppose that if someone were to get harmed or ill, they would laugh about it and say, “I’m broken,” since they are not in good health. It is something that individuals frequently state when they are struggling. Since they are unable to manage their emotions, they may declare, “I’m broken. There is another another interpretation, namely that you are poor.

We created a t-shirt with the topic “I’m Broken” today. If you don’t buy it, it will be a loss since this concept is too moving to explain. Inform your close friends, family members, and neighbors. Get this shirt now; don’t pass it up!

The global light therapy market was estimated to be US$ 1.06 Billion in 2022 and is expected grow at a CAGR of 5.1% between 2023 to 2032.

Light therapy is gaining popularity as a non-invasive and drug-free treatment option for various conditions, including skin diseases and disorders, depression, and sleep disorders. The increasing prevalence of these conditions, along with the rising demand for natural and holistic treatment options, is driving the demand for light therapy.

Following are some of the major trends in these regions- In North America, the market is driven by the high prevalence of skin diseases and disorders, as well as the rising demand for non-invasive and drug-free treatment options.

media.altText: As I get close to turning 32 I am coming to peace with the fact that I have another mental disorder I have to  understand within myself.  Not only do I hear voices in my head and have ongoing conversations with them and even think they are very real, but I also have to adjust to the norm  society has put into this. To tell you the truth I simply believe I can talk to spirits, demons, and my ex who in fact is still very alive, but very gone out of my life. Oddly he was the one who triggered my schizo to come out and play as a little happy  kid comes out and plays during lunch break at school. Yes I am a single Mother of 4, yes I fully sustain on my own my own place where it's just the kiddos and myself. Fully independent but still fully crazy as well.
